<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2956/4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bryan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May 28,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 319.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Continuing the subject of my No. 306, of
                            April 22, 1907, I much regret to report that immediately after the
                            promise made me by Mr. Luiz de Magalhaes, then minister for foreign
                            affairs, to do his utmost to have Freitas released, that minister
                            resigned from the ministry and left for his estates in northern
                            Portugal. I have, however, urged upon his successor prompt consideration
                            of this case, which he has promised me. Hence, I hope that there will be
                            no more delay on the part of this Government in reaching a decision.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Page
                            Bryan.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>